title: Meet Circus Boy
description: An evil sollicitor and his boys vows revenge on Big Tim Champion after a brawl. Champion want to send Corky to a school, however his uncle Joey want to take care of him. On the road, they received a tip that Champion would be attacked by the same mob...

title: The Fabulous Colonel Jack
description: Corky meets a retired elephant trainer and Mr Champion hires him. However, some bad luck comes along the way with his presence, mostly rain, fire in the menagerie, and a tiger on the loose.

title: The Great Gambino
description: A lion trainer, the Great Gambino, gets attacked by one of his felines due to his violent ways, and has Big Tim Champion thinks about this performer's future.

title: The Amazing Mr. Sinbad
description: As an arrogant horse rider gives Corky a hard time for several reasons, he decides to run away from the circus. As the crew looks for him, he befriends an officers who breeds a camel named Mr. Sinbad.

title: Corky and the Circus Doctor
description: A circus veterinarian arrives in time to avoid a county officer to quarantine the Circus' winter quarters, however, this decision's might affect Pop's animal responsibilities...

title: Casey Rides Again
description: With the bridge out after a thunderstorm, the Burke & Walsch circus won't make it to Carson City in time for the Territorial Day celebration. Corky suggests his new friend Casey Perkings could transport the entire troupe using his steam engine No 1. However, neither the old engine nor the track to Carson City have been made use of in years, leading to several obstacles along the way.

title: The Little Fugitive
description: A friend asks for Joey's help to impress his fiancee's son.

title: The Proud Pagliacci
description: A former circus clown who works for a rich stable owner and his snooty daughter gets hired by the circus again after losing his job due to an incident.

title: The Masked Marvel
description: A marksman called "The Masked Marvel" is the new attraction to the show. However, a couple of shady men with whom he worked before approaches him for some "job" in which he does not want to be involved.

title: The Good Samaritans
description: A town councilman's opposition threatens the Christmas performance.

title: Daring Young Man
description: Cal takes the high-diver position.

title: Farewell to the Circus
description: Corky's Aunt Martha takes him away from the circus to live with her.

title: Elmer the Aeronaut
description: Corky and Elmer find trouble while building a hot air balloon.

title: The Remarkable Ricardo
description: Ricardo is suspected of being a thief.

title: Corky's Big Parade
description: Trouble ensues, after Rip refuses to pay a bribe to a crooked politician, whom is banning the circus from entering "his" town.

title: The Lady and the Circus
description: Big Tim Champion makes plans to sell the circus and marry Rosemary Anderson, the love of his life.

title: Counterfeit Clown
description: A crook dresses up as Joey, the Clown.

title: The Fortune Teller
description: A little old lady, who reads tea leaf fortunes, joins the circus as a cook.

title: Royal Roustabout
description: A rich kid of foreign royal extraction runs away from home to join the circus.

title: Bimbo Jr.
description: Captain Jack shows up with a surprise for the circus: a baby elephant from India. The elder Bimbo soon becomes jealous of the attention given to Bimbo Jr., and runs away from the circus.

title: The Magic Lantern
description: Elmer Purdy invents a moving picture machine he calls a magic lantern.

title: Uncle Cyrus
description: Pete receives a visit from his rich Uncle Cyrus, who believes that his nephew owns the circus. With the help of Tim, Pete pretends to be the big boss.

title: The Judge's Boy
description: A judge's son runs away from home to join the circus.

title: The Return of Buffalo Bill
description: Buffalo Bill Cody blames the circus for the death of his son.
